      "id": "dec_68f0260fc3ec40f19ae2934c0ec7f9a9",
      "kind": "constraint",
      "summary": "**Root cause of the mistake:** I conflated \"the subagent couldn't access the tool\" with \"I don't have the tool.\" The skill `superpowers:dispatching-parallel-agents` acts as an orchestrator framework — it said it *needs* the Agent tool (for dispatching), and I have the Agent tool. I got confused because the skill's internal reasoning mentioned the tool wasn't accessible to a subagent, but I'm the orchestrator, not the subagent. **Fix:** When a skill says \"X tool is required and only available in environment Y,\" I should check if I (as orchestrator) have that tool directly, rather than inferring I don't because a subagent couldn't reach it. Now dispatching the adversarial agents properly:",
      "details": "**Root cause of the mistake:** I conflated \"the subagent couldn't access the tool\" with \"I don't have the tool.\" The skill `superpowers:dispatching-parallel-agents` acts as an orchestrator framework — it said it *needs* the Agent tool (for dispatching), and I have the Agent tool. I got confused because the skill's internal reasoning mentioned the tool wasn't accessible to a subagent, but I'm the orchestrator, not the subagent. **Fix:** When a skill says \"X tool is required and only available in environment Y,\" I should check if I (as orchestrator) have that tool directly, rather than inferring I don't because a subagent couldn't reach it. Now dispatching the adversarial agents properly:",
